<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3958] CMake WITH_MT option for windows static runtime linking does not support the cmake build type RelWithDebInfo</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3958</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is code in DefinePlatformSpecifc.cmake (note the file name has a typo in it) that allows one to set -DWITH_MT=ON and that will force the build to use a static runtime link.  This works for debug and release builds, but not for RelWithDebInfo builds because the list in the cmake file is incomplete.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to switch to the ucm.cmake tools to make this a bit easier, but to fix this just a couple lines need to be added to that define cmake.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Visual Studio 2010, CMake 3.6&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
